1
00:01:03,797 --> 00:01:06,266
In the first half of the 20th century,

2
00:01:06,500 --> 00:01:08,525
the people of Taiwan
underwent modernization

3
00:01:08,769 --> 00:01:10,703
under Japan's colonial rule.

4
00:01:12,739 --> 00:01:15,174
But with the empire going into war,

5
00:01:15,409 --> 00:01:17,707
Taiwanese people also
experienced miseries

6
00:01:17,945 --> 00:01:19,538
and devastations from wars.

7
00:01:20,948 --> 00:01:23,383
They prayed for the war to end

8
00:01:23,817 --> 00:01:26,081
but were uncertain and worried

9
00:01:26,320 --> 00:01:28,914
about the future it may bring.

10
00:01:49,576 --> 00:01:51,271
At the end of World War II,

11
00:01:51,511 --> 00:01:53,912
the U.S. bombarded Taiwan's

12
00:01:54,147 --> 00:01:57,310
military and industrial bases
with B-29s

13
00:02:01,888 --> 00:02:03,720
and dropped handbills
to call people

14
00:02:03,957 --> 00:02:06,449
to revolt against Japanese rule.

15
00:02:06,793 --> 00:02:09,421
Over 100,000 of these
handbills were distributed.

16
00:02:21,708 --> 00:02:23,176
Sir...

17
00:02:23,844 --> 00:02:24,936
Sir...

18
00:02:31,351 --> 00:02:35,151
Wars cause the destruction
of public facilities,

19
00:02:35,389 --> 00:02:40,384
shortage of food
and the spread of diseases.

20
00:02:40,627 --> 00:02:45,030
The best way

21
00:02:45,298 --> 00:02:45,958
to prevent the problems
from worsening

22
00:02:46,199 --> 00:02:48,190
is to stop the war.

23
00:02:48,468 --> 00:02:52,200
China and the U.S. cooperated

24
00:02:52,706 --> 00:02:55,141
in the Pacific
to defeat the Japanese

25
00:02:55,442 --> 00:02:59,879
for Taiwan's freedom.

26
00:03:05,752 --> 00:03:08,483
On August 6th and 9th of 1945,

27
00:03:08,722 --> 00:03:10,349
the U.S. dropped
two atomic bombs

28
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:13,457
on Hiroshima and Nagasaki,
respectively.

29
00:03:23,070 --> 00:03:23,764
Six days later,

30
00:03:24,004 --> 00:03:25,233
on the 15th of August,

31
00:03:25,472 --> 00:03:27,770
Emperor Showa's surrender speech

32
00:03:28,008 --> 00:03:29,999
was broadcasted over the radio

33
00:03:30,243 --> 00:03:32,575
to the people of Japan,

34
00:03:34,314 --> 00:03:36,214
which marked the end of the war.

35
00:03:36,683 --> 00:03:38,048
After 50 years of

36
00:03:38,285 --> 00:03:40,014
colonial rule under Japan,

37
00:03:40,320 --> 00:03:42,652
the people of Taiwan
was about to face a new era.

38
00:03:42,889 --> 00:03:45,620
I unconditionally accept
the Potsdam Declaration.

39
00:03:45,859 --> 00:03:48,226
It hurts me to see
my people suffer,

40
00:03:48,462 --> 00:03:49,952
so I endure the unendurable.

41
00:03:50,197 --> 00:03:51,995
You have to wait for the right time.

42
00:03:52,232 --> 00:03:53,256
Do not act rashly.

43
00:03:53,500 --> 00:03:55,798
We won...

44
00:03:56,470 --> 00:03:57,960
We won.

45
00:04:30,937 --> 00:04:31,961
After Japan's surrender,

46
00:04:32,205 --> 00:04:33,639
all the Japanese in Taiwan,
were deported back home.

47
00:04:33,874 --> 00:04:36,673
Only the technicians

48
00:04:36,977 --> 00:04:39,571
could stay temporarily.

49
00:04:40,046 --> 00:04:41,411
Among them,

50
00:04:41,648 --> 00:04:43,548
36,600 were soldiers

51
00:04:43,884 --> 00:04:46,319
and approximately
500,000 were civilians.

52
00:04:46,753 --> 00:04:48,778
All personal properties
were confiscated.

53
00:04:49,589 --> 00:04:50,681
Each person was only allowed

54
00:04:50,924 --> 00:04:53,018
to carry three pieces of luggage.

55
00:04:53,927 --> 00:04:56,589
The first ship left
on December 25, 1945.

56
00:04:56,830 --> 00:04:58,594
The deportation didn't end

57
00:04:58,832 --> 00:05:01,995
until April of the next year.

58
00:05:05,438 --> 00:05:06,530
Japan was defeated

59
00:05:06,773 --> 00:05:08,707
and Taiwan was returned to China.

60
00:05:09,042 --> 00:05:10,237
The people of Taiwan

61
00:05:10,477 --> 00:05:12,775
were no longer Japanese
but Chinese again.

62
00:05:18,919 --> 00:05:20,353
According to our position

63
00:05:20,587 --> 00:05:23,318
I officially declare
the establishment of

64
00:05:23,557 --> 00:05:24,490
the Three Principals of
the People Youth League.

65
00:05:24,724 --> 00:05:25,691
Self-motivated community leaders

66
00:05:25,926 --> 00:05:28,827
and young intellects

67
00:05:29,062 --> 00:05:29,620
formed local youth leagues

68
00:05:29,863 --> 00:05:32,457
and vigilante groups

69
00:05:32,699 --> 00:05:34,189
all across Taiwan

70
00:05:34,734 --> 00:05:35,929
to uphold public order
and security

71
00:05:36,169 --> 00:05:39,332
by patrolling the streets.

72
00:05:40,140 --> 00:05:41,835
Public properties were thus

73
00:05:42,075 --> 00:05:44,237
saved from theft and destruction.

74
00:05:44,544 --> 00:05:46,103
Water and electricity
were provided as usual,

75
00:05:46,346 --> 00:05:49,008
and railroad transportation
was smooth.

76
00:05:51,017 --> 00:05:51,916
This one is good.

77
00:05:52,953 --> 00:05:54,182
Let me see.

78
00:05:55,722 --> 00:05:56,655
Local groups welcomed the

79
00:05:56,890 --> 00:05:59,450
establishment of a KMT
organizing committee

80
00:05:59,693 --> 00:06:01,718
and exercise some
political influence.

81
00:06:02,529 --> 00:06:04,463
This group was started
by Chen Hsin,

82
00:06:04,698 --> 00:06:06,689
the pioneer of Taiwanese banking.

83
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:08,423
Since the Japanese occupation.

84
00:06:08,768 --> 00:06:11,066
It brought together
national movement activists

85
00:06:11,304 --> 00:06:13,671
such as Lin Hsien-Tang
and Yeh Jung-Chung.

86
00:06:17,644 --> 00:06:19,612
In addition to welcoming
the fatherland,

87
00:06:19,846 --> 00:06:21,837
the preparatory committee
is also committed to

88
00:06:22,282 --> 00:06:24,944
maintaining peace and order.

89
00:06:25,552 --> 00:06:26,713
Taiwan was able to come through

90
00:06:26,953 --> 00:06:28,478
the confusion during the 50 days

91
00:06:28,788 --> 00:06:30,722
of the regime transfer,

92
00:06:30,957 --> 00:06:31,947
due to the effort of

93
00:06:32,192 --> 00:06:33,819
these young intellectuals

94
00:06:34,060 --> 00:06:36,427
and community leaders.

95
00:06:43,603 --> 00:06:46,470
In "Golden Dewdrop,"

96
00:06:46,706 --> 00:06:47,332
writer Wu Cho-Liu described

97
00:06:47,574 --> 00:06:49,508
how the people in Taiwan feel
when waiting for

98
00:06:49,743 --> 00:06:51,404
"the fatherland” to take over.

99
00:06:52,045 --> 00:06:52,637
Shih. (Chinese phonic symbol)

100
00:06:52,879 --> 00:06:53,971
Shih.

101
00:06:54,447 --> 00:06:55,107
Chi.

102
00:06:55,348 --> 00:06:56,645
Chi.

103
00:06:57,350 --> 00:07:00,047
Six million people began to study

104
00:07:00,287 --> 00:07:03,552
Mandarin Chinese with fervor.

105
00:07:03,857 --> 00:07:06,155
Those who knew how to speak it

106
00:07:06,459 --> 00:07:07,290
offered their services

107
00:07:07,527 --> 00:07:10,792
as voluntary teachers

108
00:07:11,031 --> 00:07:14,023
at Chinese study centers.

109
00:07:14,267 --> 00:07:16,167
People wanted to make Taiwan

110
00:07:16,403 --> 00:07:18,701
a better place than
it was under Japan's rule.

111
00:07:18,939 --> 00:07:21,601
Please have some water.

112
00:07:22,442 --> 00:07:24,069
Is that correct?

113
00:07:24,911 --> 00:07:25,673
Not bad.

114
00:07:31,918 --> 00:07:32,817
On October 17th,

115
00:07:33,053 --> 00:07:35,351
Chinese troops entered Taipei
from Keelung

116
00:07:35,588 --> 00:07:37,818
aboard an expropriated
Japanese vessel

117
00:07:38,191 --> 00:07:41,024
escorted by the
U.S. Seventh Fleet.

118
00:07:41,695 --> 00:07:43,891
Taiwanese people welcomed

119
00:07:44,130 --> 00:07:45,359
these officials and troops
from the fatherland

120
00:07:45,598 --> 00:07:47,464
with a frenzied passion.

121
00:07:48,234 --> 00:07:49,133
Crowds gathered in
the Keelung Harbor.

122
00:07:49,369 --> 00:07:52,498
And the streets of Taipei.

123
00:08:01,214 --> 00:08:03,706
As the troops disembarked,

124
00:08:03,950 --> 00:08:04,815
people realized it was not like

125
00:08:05,051 --> 00:08:07,748
what they had imagined.

126
00:08:23,503 --> 00:08:26,063
On October 25, 1945,
a Japanese representative

127
00:08:26,306 --> 00:08:27,000
signed to surrender
at Zhongshan Hall in Taipei.

128
00:08:27,240 --> 00:08:32,770
Taiwan and Penghu were returned.

129
00:08:33,213 --> 00:08:35,238
After 50 years in enemy's hands,

130
00:08:35,482 --> 00:08:36,916
Taiwan has finally
returned to the fatherland.

131
00:08:37,150 --> 00:08:38,675
Fellow Taiwanese countrymen

132
00:08:38,918 --> 00:08:39,942
have regained their freedom

133
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:41,347
and given a new life.

134
00:08:41,588 --> 00:08:42,487
On October 25,

135
00:08:42,722 --> 00:08:45,191
the ceremony of
accepting Japan's surrender

136
00:08:45,425 --> 00:08:47,792
was held at the Taipei City Hall.

137
00:08:48,261 --> 00:08:50,229
The representative
from Taiwan and Penghu

138
00:08:50,463 --> 00:08:53,398
was Chief Executive Chen Yi.

139
00:08:53,633 --> 00:08:54,657
The surrender was signed by

140
00:08:54,901 --> 00:08:58,337
ex-Governor-General Ando Rikichi.

141
00:08:59,472 --> 00:09:02,237
Mr. Lin Mosei

142
00:09:02,475 --> 00:09:04,466
was Taiwan's representative.

143
00:09:04,744 --> 00:09:07,111
Lin was the first doctor
of philosophy in Taiwan.

144
00:09:07,347 --> 00:09:10,180
He was claimed missing
in the 228 Incident.

145
00:09:10,483 --> 00:09:11,917
His son, Lin Tsung-Yi, said

146
00:09:12,152 --> 00:09:14,849
at an interview on the 228 Incident...

147
00:09:16,222 --> 00:09:18,452
On October 25th of that year,

148
00:09:18,691 --> 00:09:22,184
Taiwan celebrated
its first Retrocession Day.

149
00:09:24,330 --> 00:09:27,391
That evening at the
Taipei City Hall party,

150
00:09:27,967 --> 00:09:29,264
my father raised his arms high.

151
00:09:29,502 --> 00:09:32,164
He said that the time has come

152
00:09:32,405 --> 00:09:33,497
for us to be our own masters.

153
00:09:34,307 --> 00:09:35,741
In that picture,

154
00:09:36,109 --> 00:09:38,510
my father wore an overcoat
with a mandarin jacket.

155
00:09:38,745 --> 00:09:40,804
He looked glad and confident,

156
00:09:41,047 --> 00:09:42,139
so full of life.

157
00:09:42,649 --> 00:09:44,208
I'll never forget that.

158
00:09:55,261 --> 00:09:57,559
Tsai Chung-Lin,

159
00:09:57,797 --> 00:09:59,265
a Hakka train conductor
in Hsinchu at the time,

160
00:09:59,499 --> 00:10:01,467
had this to say
about the KMT government

161
00:10:01,701 --> 00:10:04,033
at an interview in 2001.

162
00:10:04,404 --> 00:10:06,236
Taiwan is returned to its fatherland.

163
00:10:06,473 --> 00:10:07,133
Our fatherland should
do something

164
00:10:07,373 --> 00:10:09,137
to make our lives better.

165
00:10:09,742 --> 00:10:11,005
But the Chinese troops

166
00:10:11,244 --> 00:10:13,110
care nothing for the law.

167
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:16,472
When the Japanese ruled us,

168
00:10:16,716 --> 00:10:17,842
it was called colonization.

169
00:10:18,084 --> 00:10:19,518
With the KMT government,

170
00:10:19,786 --> 00:10:21,618
it's still colonization.

171
00:10:22,455 --> 00:10:24,583
Of course the people are angry.

172
00:10:25,391 --> 00:10:26,916
Once I drove the train

173
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:28,821
through the Hukou Station
in Hsinchu.

174
00:10:29,062 --> 00:10:30,427
There is a big slope there.

175
00:10:30,663 --> 00:10:32,427
The station supervisor
was signaling me

176
00:10:32,665 --> 00:10:33,655
to stop from afar.

177
00:10:33,900 --> 00:10:34,332
He ran up and told me that

178
00:10:34,567 --> 00:10:36,035
a soldier needed to get on.

179
00:10:36,503 --> 00:10:37,561
Just for one person.

180
00:10:38,538 --> 00:10:39,801
I didn't want to do it,

181
00:10:40,340 --> 00:10:42,069
but he begged me

182
00:10:42,308 --> 00:10:44,242
and said that
the soldier threatened him.

183
00:10:44,677 --> 00:10:46,406
If the train didn't stop

184
00:10:46,746 --> 00:10:48,771
he would gather some people

185
00:10:49,015 --> 00:10:50,005
and shoot me dead.

186
00:10:50,250 --> 00:10:51,217
He got on and sat

187
00:10:51,684 --> 00:10:53,311
on the seat next to me.

188
00:10:53,553 --> 00:10:54,611
The train went up the slope,

189
00:10:54,854 --> 00:10:55,912
but couldn't make it over.

190
00:10:56,156 --> 00:10:57,487
I asked everybody to
help push the train,

191
00:10:58,124 --> 00:10:59,558
but he just sat there.

192
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,787
During the Japanese Occupation,

193
00:11:02,028 --> 00:11:04,258
the soldiers weren't like that,

194
00:11:04,497 --> 00:11:06,864
no matter how high
their ranks were.

195
00:11:13,873 --> 00:11:15,841
People help each other.

196
00:11:37,997 --> 00:11:40,762
Chen Yi was appointed
Chief Executive

197
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,968
and Garrison Commander
of Taiwan.

198
00:11:43,336 --> 00:11:46,203
He had visited the island in 1935

199
00:11:46,739 --> 00:11:48,673
and highly praised the way

200
00:11:48,908 --> 00:11:50,069
the Japanese ruled it.

201
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:52,910
He believed that the key
to success lied in

202
00:11:53,146 --> 00:11:54,807
the government's control
of economic resources.

203
00:11:56,316 --> 00:11:59,183
So, in addition to holding

204
00:11:59,419 --> 00:12:01,751
administrative, legislative, judicial,

205
00:12:01,988 --> 00:12:04,286
and military power,

206
00:12:04,657 --> 00:12:06,557
the Taiwan Provincial
Governor Office took over

207
00:12:06,793 --> 00:12:09,387
large and medium enterprises
left by the Japanese.

208
00:12:09,929 --> 00:12:11,419
Political, economical

209
00:12:11,664 --> 00:12:12,756
and social resources were

210
00:12:12,999 --> 00:12:15,798
systematically monopolized.

211
00:12:24,477 --> 00:12:26,104
Although the KMT government

212
00:12:26,346 --> 00:12:28,440
allowed the Taiwanese people
to participate in politics,

213
00:12:28,715 --> 00:12:29,341
in actuality,

214
00:12:29,582 --> 00:12:32,210
they denied many well-educated

215
00:12:32,452 --> 00:12:32,941
Taiwanese citizens

216
00:12:33,186 --> 00:12:35,678
from serving high
government posts

217
00:12:35,922 --> 00:12:38,357
on reasons that
they did not speak Mandarin

218
00:12:38,591 --> 00:12:41,356
or that Taiwan did not have
any political talents.

219
00:12:42,528 --> 00:12:44,656
On October 28, 1946,
an editorial in the

220
00:12:44,897 --> 00:12:46,092
Taiwan People's Newspaper titled

221
00:12:46,332 --> 00:12:49,199
“Preventing the Yearend
Crisis” said

222
00:12:51,571 --> 00:12:52,129
Everyday, I see promising
young men

223
00:12:52,372 --> 00:12:55,034
going about looking for jobs.

224
00:12:55,275 --> 00:12:56,606
They call on seniors and friends.

225
00:12:56,843 --> 00:12:58,402
They all sighed,

226
00:12:58,711 --> 00:13:01,043
shaking their heads and say
it's just the way it is.

227
00:13:01,514 --> 00:13:03,482
All the important heads
of the government,

228
00:13:03,716 --> 00:13:05,377
companies and factories

229
00:13:05,618 --> 00:13:07,780
were people they do not know.

230
00:13:09,555 --> 00:13:10,044
This was what Chen Feng-Yuan,

231
00:13:10,290 --> 00:13:12,725
who participated in the

232
00:13:12,959 --> 00:13:15,087
establishment of Taiwan Trust,

233
00:13:15,328 --> 00:13:17,126
said at a 1991 interview.

234
00:13:18,131 --> 00:13:19,565
When Taiwan was retroceded

235
00:13:19,799 --> 00:13:20,960
we were all very happy.

236
00:13:21,467 --> 00:13:24,232
But later we were disappointed.

237
00:13:24,837 --> 00:13:27,397
Many government officials
were corrupt.

238
00:13:28,041 --> 00:13:29,202
We all said that the take-over

239
00:13:29,442 --> 00:13:32,070
was literally taking over
everything we own.

240
00:13:34,647 --> 00:13:37,878
News of corruptions
were common at the time.

241
00:13:39,052 --> 00:13:41,987
At the Taiwan Provincial Senate,

242
00:13:42,221 --> 00:13:43,586
Congressmen Wang Tien-Teng
and Lin Ji-Kao exposed

243
00:13:43,823 --> 00:13:46,758
the crime of embezzlement
of goods and materials

244
00:13:46,993 --> 00:13:49,792
by directors of the Monopoly
Bureau and Trade Bureau.

245
00:13:50,029 --> 00:13:52,794
Chen Yi cares very much

246
00:13:53,232 --> 00:13:55,599
about the Taiwanese people.

247
00:13:56,402 --> 00:13:58,131
Taiwanese people are grateful

248
00:13:58,705 --> 00:14:01,606
for his concerns.

249
00:14:02,041 --> 00:14:04,510
But unfortunately,

250
00:14:04,911 --> 00:14:08,905
most of the officials aren't like him.

251
00:14:09,148 --> 00:14:12,118
All they care about is the
money Taiwan can bring them.

252
00:14:14,287 --> 00:14:15,982
Did you know that the
Monopoly Bureau

253
00:14:16,489 --> 00:14:19,186
reimbursed 70 kilos of opium?

254
00:14:23,763 --> 00:14:26,027
I heard they were eaten by termites.

255
00:14:29,302 --> 00:14:31,202
If that's the case,

256
00:14:31,437 --> 00:14:33,064
then I suggest we call

257
00:14:33,306 --> 00:14:35,240
a few well-known
scientists and doctors

258
00:14:35,475 --> 00:14:36,465
to check and see

259
00:14:37,410 --> 00:14:40,380
if termites indeed eat opium.

260
00:14:41,514 --> 00:14:44,006
Later it was proved that they don't.

261
00:14:44,684 --> 00:14:46,652
It was eaten up by what the
people call Big Tigers

262
00:14:46,886 --> 00:14:48,718
or high officials
with power and influence.

263
00:15:10,510 --> 00:15:12,000
After the KMT took over,

264
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:13,940
with the expansion of
state-run enterprises bigger

265
00:15:14,180 --> 00:15:16,911
than these under
Japanese Occupation

266
00:15:17,183 --> 00:15:19,845
and the corruption
of government officials,

267
00:15:20,086 --> 00:15:21,781
the guidance of amateurs leaders,

268
00:15:22,021 --> 00:15:23,250
led to bad management.

269
00:15:23,489 --> 00:15:25,981
Prices soared;

270
00:15:26,426 --> 00:15:27,416
the economy recessed;

271
00:15:27,660 --> 00:15:28,684
people lived in destitution;

272
00:15:28,928 --> 00:15:30,828
thefts were commonplace;

273
00:15:31,130 --> 00:15:32,029
public security worsened;

274
00:15:32,265 --> 00:15:34,165
and violence existed everywhere.

275
00:15:34,400 --> 00:15:35,526
Things were getting out of control.

276
00:15:40,473 --> 00:15:41,133
Get him.

277
00:15:41,374 --> 00:15:42,136
Arrest him.

278
00:15:42,508 --> 00:15:43,168
What are you doing?

279
00:15:43,409 --> 00:15:44,001
Is this a revolt?

280
00:15:44,243 --> 00:15:45,039
What revolt?

281
00:15:45,278 --> 00:15:46,302
I don't know
what you're talking about.

282
00:15:46,546 --> 00:15:47,274
Let go...

283
00:15:47,513 --> 00:15:48,912
Let go of what? I don't understand.

284
00:15:49,148 --> 00:15:49,944
Are you picking on we Taiwanese?

285
00:15:50,183 --> 00:15:50,945
Hey.

286
00:15:52,018 --> 00:15:52,576
Hey what?

287
00:15:52,819 --> 00:15:53,479
Hey, I don't understand.

288
00:15:53,719 --> 00:15:54,311
Hey.

289
00:15:55,922 --> 00:15:57,083
Don't pick on us.

290
00:15:58,357 --> 00:15:59,654
Guns...

291
00:16:01,828 --> 00:16:03,990
Under such hard condition,

292
00:16:04,230 --> 00:16:06,426
misunderstandings between
the Taiwanese and mainlanders

293
00:16:06,666 --> 00:16:08,031
are getting worse and worse.

294
00:16:08,835 --> 00:16:11,327
After 50 years of colonization,

295
00:16:11,571 --> 00:16:13,061
Taiwan had adopted many
Japanese characteristics.

296
00:16:13,306 --> 00:16:14,432
How they speak and behave

297
00:16:14,674 --> 00:16:16,073
and how they treat each other

298
00:16:16,309 --> 00:16:18,300
were influenced by
the Japanese people.

299
00:16:27,753 --> 00:16:29,687
The Chinese soldiers,

300
00:16:29,922 --> 00:16:31,549
who had just fought
the eight-year war,

301
00:16:31,791 --> 00:16:32,917
did not like

302
00:16:33,159 --> 00:16:34,558
this foreign flair.

303
00:16:34,994 --> 00:16:36,894
They said that
the Taiwanese people

304
00:16:37,129 --> 00:16:38,619
behaved like slaves.

305
00:16:39,499 --> 00:16:41,263
The Taiwanese resented
the mainlanders

306
00:16:41,501 --> 00:16:43,265
even more after that

307
00:16:43,503 --> 00:16:44,971
and this turned into a vicious cycle.

308
00:16:45,805 --> 00:16:48,570
After 50 years of Japanese rule,

309
00:16:48,808 --> 00:16:50,606
barriers against mainland culture

310
00:16:50,843 --> 00:16:52,242
appeared

311
00:16:52,478 --> 00:16:54,003
resulting in maladjustment.

312
00:17:03,556 --> 00:17:05,718
Friction between the two groups

313
00:17:05,958 --> 00:17:08,222
worsened gradually.

314
00:17:08,561 --> 00:17:10,825
During a search
for illegal cigarettes,

315
00:17:11,063 --> 00:17:13,691
the mounting tension

316
00:17:13,933 --> 00:17:15,867
finally erupted into

317
00:17:16,102 --> 00:17:18,366
a tragedy in the history of Taiwan.

318
00:17:37,256 --> 00:17:38,280
Come and buy some.

319
00:17:38,524 --> 00:17:43,928
Come and buy some steamed buns.

320
00:17:44,163 --> 00:17:45,130
Buy some sweet fruit.

321
00:17:45,364 --> 00:17:46,490
Come on.

322
00:17:46,799 --> 00:17:49,666
On the evening of February 27, 1947,

323
00:17:49,902 --> 00:17:51,734
Fu Hsueh-Tung and five
anti-smuggling officers

324
00:17:51,971 --> 00:17:53,530
of the Monopoly Bureau,

325
00:17:53,773 --> 00:17:55,366
were on duty in Taiping District,
Taipei

326
00:17:55,608 --> 00:17:58,441
which is now Nanking West Road.

327
00:17:59,211 --> 00:18:01,270
They found Lin Chiang-Mai,
a middle-aged widow,

328
00:18:01,514 --> 00:18:04,108
selling illegal cigarettes in
front of Tian Ma Tea House.

329
00:18:07,853 --> 00:18:08,786
The officers wanted

330
00:18:09,021 --> 00:18:10,420
to confiscate the cigarettes

331
00:18:10,656 --> 00:18:12,146
and all the money she had with her.

332
00:18:12,525 --> 00:18:13,993
Lin begged them

333
00:18:14,226 --> 00:18:15,660
not to do so.

334
00:18:16,062 --> 00:18:18,861
They hit her head with their guns

335
00:18:19,098 --> 00:18:20,532
until she fell on the ground

336
00:18:20,766 --> 00:18:22,200
bleeding and crying with pain.

337
00:18:27,073 --> 00:18:29,565
Witnesses were enraged

338
00:18:29,809 --> 00:18:31,299
and protested against the officers,

339
00:18:32,078 --> 00:18:33,773
who ran away in panic

340
00:18:34,046 --> 00:18:35,536
firing their guns
to show their authority.

341
00:18:35,781 --> 00:18:38,614
A bystander Chen Wen-His
was unfortunately shot

342
00:18:39,352 --> 00:18:40,751
and killed, which further
angered the crowd.

343
00:18:40,987 --> 00:18:42,955
They surrounded police
and military police stations

344
00:18:43,222 --> 00:18:45,020
and demanded them to
hand over the perpetrator,

345
00:18:45,257 --> 00:18:46,554
but to no avail.

346
00:18:50,396 --> 00:18:51,693
Police murderer.

347
00:18:51,931 --> 00:18:53,228
Hand over the perpetrator.

348
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:56,090
Police murderer.

349
00:18:56,335 --> 00:18:57,166
Hand over the perpetrator.

350
00:18:57,403 --> 00:18:58,529
On the morning of the 28th,

351
00:18:58,771 --> 00:18:59,465
people gathered outside the

352
00:18:59,705 --> 00:19:02,003
Monopoly Bureau to protest.

353
00:19:02,274 --> 00:19:04,902
They threw paperwork
and office supplies

354
00:19:05,144 --> 00:19:06,737
out onto the street
and burned them.

355
00:19:06,979 --> 00:19:08,572
They also beat up
a couple of employees.

356
00:19:09,915 --> 00:19:11,007
Burn them all.

357
00:19:11,250 --> 00:19:11,944
Come on.

358
00:19:14,487 --> 00:19:15,921
Later in the afternoon,
the crowd moved onto

359
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:19,318
the square in front of the
Taiwan Provincial Governor Office.

360
00:19:19,792 --> 00:19:21,282
The military police
on the building's balcony

361
00:19:21,527 --> 00:19:23,552
swept the crowd with machine guns

362
00:19:23,796 --> 00:19:25,127
and dozens of people were killed.

363
00:19:50,022 --> 00:19:50,716
By now,

364
00:19:50,956 --> 00:19:52,822
things were already out of control.

365
00:19:53,059 --> 00:19:54,049
The city was in an uproar;

366
00:19:54,293 --> 00:19:55,317
shops were closed;

367
00:19:55,561 --> 00:19:56,653
factories were shot down;

368
00:19:56,896 --> 00:19:58,227
students refused to go to school.

369
00:19:58,464 --> 00:20:01,058
The Taiwan Garrison Command
imposed martial law.

370
00:20:01,300 --> 00:20:03,359
Young people went to
radio stations

371
00:20:03,602 --> 00:20:06,162
to broadcast the story on air

372
00:20:06,405 --> 00:20:08,806
and asked people everywhere
to work together.

373
00:20:09,809 --> 00:20:11,743
Today, the 28th of February,

374
00:20:11,977 --> 00:20:14,969
people went to the
Governor Office to protest.

375
00:20:15,247 --> 00:20:16,078
Chen Yi and his administration

376
00:20:16,315 --> 00:20:18,807
should fire at them
with machine guns

377
00:20:19,051 --> 00:20:20,849
and kill our people.

378
00:20:21,420 --> 00:20:22,649
Retribution!

379
00:20:22,888 --> 00:20:23,616
Hand over the perpetrator!

380
00:20:23,856 --> 00:20:24,914
Hand over the perpetrator!

381
00:20:25,157 --> 00:20:25,885
Retribution!

382
00:20:26,125 --> 00:20:27,286
Retribution!

383
00:20:32,331 --> 00:20:33,423
From March 1st,

384
00:20:33,666 --> 00:20:35,634
the protest quickly spread
across the island.

385
00:20:35,868 --> 00:20:38,496
Angry crowds attacked
the Governor Office

386
00:20:38,738 --> 00:20:39,864
and police stations,
and beat up mainlanders,

387
00:20:40,106 --> 00:20:42,165
venting the anger
that have built up over the year.

388
00:20:42,408 --> 00:20:44,069
Chen Yi declared martial law.

389
00:20:44,310 --> 00:20:46,210
The military and police fired
guns to subdue the crowds

390
00:20:46,445 --> 00:20:47,276
and you could hear news

391
00:20:47,513 --> 00:20:50,141
of casualties anytime.

392
00:20:54,920 --> 00:20:56,149
In order to appease the anger,

393
00:20:56,388 --> 00:20:57,150
the KMT representatives

394
00:20:57,389 --> 00:20:58,413
and congressmen established

395
00:20:58,657 --> 00:21:00,716
the Tobacco Search Murder
Investigation Committee

396
00:21:00,960 --> 00:21:03,725
on March 1st.

397
00:21:05,197 --> 00:21:07,723
In order to abate
the people's discontent

398
00:21:07,967 --> 00:21:10,197
and to win time to mobilize troops,

399
00:21:10,536 --> 00:21:11,435
Chen Yi agreed to form

400
00:21:11,670 --> 00:21:13,900
a committee of the 228 Incident

401
00:21:14,140 --> 00:21:16,575
to serve as the mediator

402
00:21:16,909 --> 00:21:17,842
and to tell the people

403
00:21:18,077 --> 00:21:20,045
not to hurt mainlanders.

404
00:21:27,486 --> 00:21:29,079
By March 5th,

405
00:21:29,321 --> 00:21:30,982
except for the Chiayi area,

406
00:21:31,223 --> 00:21:33,692
most of the uproars
have quieted down.

407
00:21:33,926 --> 00:21:36,691
But Chiang Kai-Shek,
head of the KMT,

408
00:21:36,929 --> 00:21:38,693
after hearing biased statements

409
00:21:38,931 --> 00:21:39,989
from secret agents in Taiwan,

410
00:21:40,232 --> 00:21:42,257
still decided to send troops
to the island.

411
00:21:49,141 --> 00:21:49,733
Everybody.

412
00:21:49,975 --> 00:21:51,033
Please calm down.

413
00:21:51,377 --> 00:21:52,811
Please listen to me.

414
00:21:53,045 --> 00:21:53,603
During a chaotic meeting

415
00:21:53,846 --> 00:21:56,281
on March 7th,

416
00:21:56,515 --> 00:21:58,882
the committee passed
the 32 Management Outlines

417
00:21:59,118 --> 00:22:00,916
proposed by Wang Tien-Teng,
the director of information.

418
00:22:01,587 --> 00:22:03,749
Which offered concrete resolutions

419
00:22:03,989 --> 00:22:05,582
and political reform proposals.

420
00:22:06,158 --> 00:22:08,058
After the meeting,
the committee took the outlines

421
00:22:08,294 --> 00:22:10,956
to Chen Yi at the Governor Office.

422
00:22:11,330 --> 00:22:12,764
Chen threw them on the ground,

423
00:22:12,998 --> 00:22:14,227
Rejecting them in anger,

424
00:22:14,466 --> 00:22:15,365
because he knew that

425
00:22:15,601 --> 00:22:18,536
the troops from Nanjing
were arriving soon.

426
00:22:24,009 --> 00:22:25,443
On the evening of March 8th,

427
00:22:25,678 --> 00:22:28,340
KMT troops landed at Keelung.

428
00:22:28,581 --> 00:22:30,777
Workers working at the harbor

429
00:22:31,016 --> 00:22:31,847
were shot dead by these men

430
00:22:32,084 --> 00:22:34,382
who appeared out of nowhere.

431
00:22:46,198 --> 00:22:47,131
On March 9th,

432
00:22:47,366 --> 00:22:49,061
the 21st Division entered Taipei

433
00:22:49,301 --> 00:22:50,860
and traveled south,

434
00:22:51,103 --> 00:22:53,299
suppressing and killing
people everywhere.

435
00:22:53,539 --> 00:22:54,836
The casualties were heavy.

436
00:22:55,374 --> 00:22:57,274
The 228 Incident Committee

437
00:22:57,509 --> 00:22:59,807
was later proclaimed to be illegal

438
00:23:00,045 --> 00:23:01,604
and dissolved by Chen Yi.

439
00:23:01,881 --> 00:23:04,441
Many of the social elites who
participated in the meeting

440
00:23:04,683 --> 00:23:07,778
were in the purge list.

441
00:23:08,220 --> 00:23:11,520
They either disappeared
or were murdered.

442
00:23:40,619 --> 00:23:41,848
On March 20th,

443
00:23:42,087 --> 00:23:43,987
the Governor Office began

444
00:23:44,223 --> 00:23:46,487
what was called the
"countryside cleansing,” to

445
00:23:46,725 --> 00:23:48,193
threaten people to turn
in weapons and perpetrators

446
00:23:48,427 --> 00:23:51,089
or to suffer collateral punishment.

447
00:23:51,330 --> 00:23:53,628
People were either arrested or shot,

448
00:23:53,866 --> 00:23:55,960
all without open trials.

449
00:23:56,235 --> 00:23:57,396
Taiwan was shrouded under

450
00:23:57,636 --> 00:23:59,536
a murderous atmosphere.

451
00:24:04,677 --> 00:24:06,111
To this day, the exact

452
00:24:06,345 --> 00:24:07,870
number of casualties

453
00:24:08,113 --> 00:24:10,241
is still uncertain.

454
00:24:10,582 --> 00:24:12,107
According to the Executive Yuan,

455
00:24:12,351 --> 00:24:13,910
the official investigation

456
00:24:14,153 --> 00:24:17,054
puts the death toll at
roughly 10,000 to 20,000.

457
00:24:26,532 --> 00:24:28,432
The 228 Incident resulted in

458
00:24:28,667 --> 00:24:31,193
more than just broken families.

459
00:24:31,503 --> 00:24:34,097
The hatred and contradiction

460
00:24:34,340 --> 00:24:35,034
Planted in the two groups
deeply affected

461
00:24:35,274 --> 00:24:37,436
Taiwan's future political trajectory.

462
00:24:38,143 --> 00:24:39,201
Years afterwards,

463
00:24:39,445 --> 00:24:41,607
many post-war literary works

464
00:24:41,847 --> 00:24:42,780
of Taiwan still focus on

465
00:24:43,015 --> 00:24:45,382
the 228 Incident, voicing

466
00:24:45,617 --> 00:24:48,245
the sorrow of the people.

467
00:25:52,851 --> 00:25:54,819
After 1949, the situation

468
00:25:55,054 --> 00:25:56,613
in Taiwan was no better.

469
00:25:56,855 --> 00:25:58,789
The tragedies didn't stop.

470
00:25:59,024 --> 00:25:59,752
The KMT government,

471
00:25:59,992 --> 00:26:01,016
through tightly organized

472
00:26:01,260 --> 00:26:05,163
intelligence system
and secret agents stationed

473
00:26:05,397 --> 00:26:06,728
in government offices and schools,

474
00:26:06,965 --> 00:26:09,434
from cities to countryside,

475
00:26:09,668 --> 00:26:11,864
strictly monitored the society

476
00:26:12,104 --> 00:26:13,538
to curb and eliminate

477
00:26:13,772 --> 00:26:15,297
any dissidents, and to

478
00:26:15,541 --> 00:26:18,306
strengthen its supreme power.

479
00:26:18,544 --> 00:26:20,205
Various powers existed in Taiwan

480
00:26:20,446 --> 00:26:21,936
were reorganized.

481
00:26:22,181 --> 00:26:23,273
They aggressively trained

482
00:26:23,515 --> 00:26:26,143
a pro-KMT faction,

483
00:26:26,385 --> 00:26:27,147
and successfully created
a monopolized

484
00:26:27,386 --> 00:26:30,083
and authoritative party in Taiwan.

485
00:26:35,828 --> 00:26:38,160
So when people were busy,

486
00:26:38,397 --> 00:26:40,331
they still remembered Ah Q.

487
00:26:40,566 --> 00:26:42,500
But they remembered his deeds

488
00:26:42,734 --> 00:26:44,259
and not his background.

489
00:26:44,503 --> 00:26:46,471
What do you guys think about that?

490
00:26:46,738 --> 00:26:48,069
That's us, isn't it?

491
00:26:48,373 --> 00:26:49,772
Ah Q...

492
00:26:50,008 --> 00:26:51,271
We're like Ah Q.

493
00:26:51,977 --> 00:26:53,308
Frogs at the bottom of a well.

494
00:26:55,781 --> 00:26:58,546
He says that Ah Q

495
00:26:59,184 --> 00:27:01,619
is not someone's...

496
00:27:01,954 --> 00:27:03,046
Who is it?

497
00:27:04,556 --> 00:27:06,024
A Hakka young man
named Chen Chuan-Chih

498
00:27:06,258 --> 00:27:08,556
was arrested
for attending a study group.

499
00:27:09,194 --> 00:27:11,322
The records of a
2001 interview showed

500
00:27:11,563 --> 00:27:12,928
this version of what happened.

501
00:27:14,133 --> 00:27:15,123
At that time,

502
00:27:15,734 --> 00:27:17,862
people didn't understand
how the KMT could have been

503
00:27:18,103 --> 00:27:19,537
driven to Taiwan by the
Communist Party

504
00:27:19,771 --> 00:27:23,139
with the advanced equipment

505
00:27:23,375 --> 00:27:24,809
the KMT took over
from the Americans.

506
00:27:25,811 --> 00:27:27,006
But once they understood,

507
00:27:27,346 --> 00:27:30,281
they resented the society.

508
00:27:30,616 --> 00:27:33,950
Those secret agents are abominable.

509
00:27:34,653 --> 00:27:35,677
Not only did they arrest the

510
00:27:36,588 --> 00:27:38,818
people at the study group,

511
00:27:40,325 --> 00:27:43,386
they also arrested their

512
00:27:43,662 --> 00:27:45,027
friends, for money.

513
00:27:45,931 --> 00:27:48,901
Some people didn't
even know how to read.

514
00:27:50,502 --> 00:27:53,563
Under the pressure from the KMT,

515
00:27:54,072 --> 00:27:57,337
both Taiwanese and

516
00:27:57,709 --> 00:27:59,302
mainlanders were arrested.

517
00:27:59,878 --> 00:28:01,346
One of these men

518
00:28:02,147 --> 00:28:04,013
was Lee Jui-Tung.

519
00:28:04,750 --> 00:28:11,679
He taught them by writing
on soaps with chopsticks.

520
00:28:12,324 --> 00:28:13,951
If someone was sick,

521
00:28:14,860 --> 00:28:17,329
he would give him medicine.

522
00:28:17,763 --> 00:28:18,821
The intellectuals who

523
00:28:19,298 --> 00:28:21,460
were executed at that time.

524
00:28:22,067 --> 00:28:25,162
Were cultivated people with

525
00:28:25,571 --> 00:28:27,471
good personalities.

526
00:28:29,775 --> 00:28:31,368
Chen Chuan-Chih, a train conductor

527
00:28:31,610 --> 00:28:32,771
like about 2000 political victims

528
00:28:33,011 --> 00:28:34,240
of White Terror,

529
00:28:34,479 --> 00:28:36,641
were executed.

530
00:28:36,882 --> 00:28:38,714
More than 8000 people
received heavy sentences.

531
00:28:38,951 --> 00:28:39,850
Among them, less than 900

532
00:28:40,085 --> 00:28:42,053
were real Communists.

533
00:28:42,321 --> 00:28:43,220
The remaining 9000 or so cases

534
00:28:43,455 --> 00:28:46,447
were either unjust,
misjudged or feigned.

535
00:28:46,692 --> 00:28:48,057
Of all the people who were killed,

536
00:28:48,293 --> 00:28:50,057
two-thirds were Taiwanese

537
00:28:50,295 --> 00:28:52,229
and one-third were mainlanders.

538
00:28:59,771 --> 00:29:01,705
In the 50s, outside the
Taipei Train Station,

539
00:29:01,940 --> 00:29:04,932
on bulletin boards,

540
00:29:05,177 --> 00:29:06,338
it was common to see lists
of names with red checks

541
00:29:06,578 --> 00:29:09,309
suggesting people being
executed for mutiny.

542
00:29:09,781 --> 00:29:12,580
Young people from different
ethnicities and provinces

543
00:29:12,818 --> 00:29:14,684
were often accused of
crimes they did not commit,

544
00:29:14,920 --> 00:29:16,445
costing their young lives,

545
00:29:16,688 --> 00:29:17,587
and sometimes even the lives

546
00:29:17,823 --> 00:29:19,587
and the happiness of their families.

547
00:29:22,828 --> 00:29:24,728
In December 1950,

548
00:29:25,030 --> 00:29:27,055
a young man from Banciao
named Lin Ju-Yu

549
00:29:27,299 --> 00:29:29,393
was executed at Machang District,

550
00:29:29,635 --> 00:29:30,830
what is now the Youth Park.

551
00:29:31,169 --> 00:29:33,570
His sister Lin Hsin-Tzu
recalls the execution.

552
00:29:34,506 --> 00:29:37,635
On Saturday,

553
00:29:37,876 --> 00:29:38,968
December 16, 1950,

554
00:29:39,511 --> 00:29:41,445
at around 7 o'clock in the morning,

555
00:29:41,713 --> 00:29:43,044
I took the train as usual

556
00:29:43,282 --> 00:29:46,217
from Banciao
to go to school in Taipei.

557
00:29:47,119 --> 00:29:48,814
As I walked out of the platform,

558
00:29:49,121 --> 00:29:51,681
I saw a crowd gathering

559
00:29:51,990 --> 00:29:54,118
in front of the bulletin board
at the Taipei Train Station.

560
00:29:54,593 --> 00:29:58,188
With a feeling of uneasiness,

561
00:29:58,430 --> 00:29:59,864
I slowly walked up to it.

562
00:30:00,098 --> 00:30:01,122
From afar,

563
00:30:01,533 --> 00:30:03,763
I saw the list of
so-called "mutineers."”

564
00:30:04,002 --> 00:30:08,701
On one of the lines

565
00:30:09,207 --> 00:30:10,902
was the name Lin Ju-Yu.

566
00:30:11,143 --> 00:30:12,372
Aged 28

567
00:30:12,744 --> 00:30:14,234
Death penalty.

568
00:30:14,479 --> 00:30:16,106
I was devastated, and didn't know

569
00:30:16,615 --> 00:30:19,414
whether I should cry or

570
00:30:19,651 --> 00:30:22,348
I should just turn and leave.

571
00:30:35,867 --> 00:30:36,993
In 1949,

572
00:30:37,235 --> 00:30:39,761
on May 20th,

573
00:30:40,105 --> 00:30:41,539
Provincial Government
Chairman Chen Cheng

574
00:30:41,773 --> 00:30:44,299
announced martial law for Taiwan.

575
00:30:44,676 --> 00:30:45,973
For 38 years,

576
00:30:46,211 --> 00:30:48,339
the island lived under
strict governance.

577
00:30:52,851 --> 00:30:53,682
Six months after

578
00:30:53,919 --> 00:30:55,785
the KMT was defeated in China.

579
00:30:56,021 --> 00:30:57,386
The republic government

580
00:30:57,656 --> 00:30:59,784
retreated to Taiwan

581
00:31:00,025 --> 00:31:01,254
with about 900,000
soldiers and civilians.

582
00:31:01,560 --> 00:31:02,925
This was a rare

583
00:31:03,161 --> 00:31:04,560
mass immigration

584
00:31:04,796 --> 00:31:06,491
in the history of the island.

585
00:31:06,798 --> 00:31:08,493
As a result,
Taiwan's population structure

586
00:31:08,734 --> 00:31:10,930
changed quantitatively
and qualitatively.

587
00:31:11,570 --> 00:31:12,969
Different cultures in this island

588
00:31:13,205 --> 00:31:15,173
once again changed and

589
00:31:15,407 --> 00:31:17,808
conflict with one another.

590
00:31:18,043 --> 00:31:19,875
This added diversity to Taiwan

591
00:31:20,112 --> 00:31:21,170
and had a great impact

592
00:31:21,413 --> 00:31:23,939
on the Taiwanese society.

593
00:31:24,649 --> 00:31:26,208
Henceforth,
the republic government

594
00:31:26,451 --> 00:31:28,010
took over Taiwan, Penghu,
Kinmen, and Matsu.

595
00:31:28,253 --> 00:31:30,085
The civil war was henceforth

596
00:31:30,322 --> 00:31:33,087
fought across the Taiwan Strait.

597
00:31:33,458 --> 00:31:34,425
Taiwan, Penghu, Kinmen and Matsu

598
00:31:34,659 --> 00:31:35,990
became world-famous

599
00:31:36,228 --> 00:31:37,957
anti-Communist
and anti-Soviet fortresses.

600
00:31:38,697 --> 00:31:41,598
The 6 million people
who lived in Taiwan,

601
00:31:41,833 --> 00:31:43,426
soldiers and civilians alike,

602
00:31:43,668 --> 00:31:45,636
became Chiang Kai-Shek's
anti-communist

603
00:31:45,871 --> 00:31:47,032
and anti-Soviet subjects

604
00:31:47,272 --> 00:31:49,900
who would give up their lives
for their country.

605
00:31:50,175 --> 00:31:52,337
After every speech Chiang makes,

606
00:31:52,577 --> 00:31:55,012
he would lead
the people on the square

607
00:31:55,247 --> 00:31:58,683
to shout "Long live the Republic.”

608
00:31:59,151 --> 00:32:01,483
The people below would
then shout

609
00:32:01,720 --> 00:32:04,087
"Long live President Chiang."

610
00:32:04,890 --> 00:32:06,688
Long live the Republic!

611
00:32:07,192 --> 00:32:08,921
Long live the Republic!

612
00:32:14,132 --> 00:32:16,931
Once in Nanjing,
Chiang Kai-Shek announced

613
00:32:17,169 --> 00:32:19,137
the Temporary Provisions
Effective During the Period

614
00:32:19,371 --> 00:32:22,238
of Communist Rebellion
which froze a portion of the constitution.

615
00:32:22,841 --> 00:32:24,070
After the relocation
of KMT in Taiwan,

616
00:32:24,309 --> 00:32:26,539
the provisions were amended

617
00:32:26,778 --> 00:32:28,712
to expand presidential power.

618
00:32:29,214 --> 00:32:31,774
Consequently,
Chiang served five terms,

619
00:32:32,017 --> 00:32:33,883
or 25 years, as president.

620
00:32:42,861 --> 00:32:44,852
Taiwan, as an interim
government under

621
00:32:45,096 --> 00:32:47,224
the banner of anti-Communist
and anti-Soviet,

622
00:32:47,466 --> 00:32:48,194
was actually under
an autocratic rule

623
00:32:48,433 --> 00:32:51,368
of coercion.

624
00:32:51,603 --> 00:32:53,628
Basic human rights and
human dignity

625
00:32:53,872 --> 00:32:55,465
were greatly suppressed.

626
00:32:55,740 --> 00:32:57,003
Meanwhile, the shadow of war

627
00:32:57,242 --> 00:32:59,472
still shrouded over Taiwan.

628
00:33:07,953 --> 00:33:09,853
On January 20, 1955.

629
00:33:10,088 --> 00:33:11,852
The Korean War had just ended.

630
00:33:12,157 --> 00:33:12,851
Taiwan became a vital stronghold

631
00:33:13,091 --> 00:33:16,061
in the US's efforts
to combat Communism.

632
00:33:16,828 --> 00:33:17,989
The Communist Party attacked
Yijiangshan Islands,

633
00:33:18,230 --> 00:33:20,562
where some KMT troops stationed.

634
00:33:20,832 --> 00:33:23,995
The US Congress immediately
passed the Formosa Resolution

635
00:33:24,236 --> 00:33:26,796
to show its determination
in defending Taiwan.

636
00:33:27,305 --> 00:33:29,103
Yet they still hoped
that Chiang Kai-Shek

637
00:33:29,341 --> 00:33:30,831
would leave the islands
off the coast of Fujien,

638
00:33:31,076 --> 00:33:33,636
and retreat from Dachen
and Zhoushan Islands.

639
00:33:34,279 --> 00:33:36,941
Chiang took the US's advice

640
00:33:37,182 --> 00:33:39,514
of relinquishing the islands,

641
00:33:40,318 --> 00:33:42,218
but the US continued
to pressure him

642
00:33:42,454 --> 00:33:44,320
to withdraw from
Kinmen and Matsu.

643
00:33:44,556 --> 00:33:47,321
But this time,
Chiang did not comply.

644
00:33:55,133 --> 00:33:57,067
On August 23, 1958,

645
00:33:57,302 --> 00:34:00,169
the PRC resumed their attacks
on Kinmen and Matsu.

646
00:34:00,438 --> 00:34:02,998
More than 40,000 bombs were
dropped in a two hours.

647
00:34:03,241 --> 00:34:05,539
Thus beganthe the Aug. 23rd
Artillery Bombardment.

648
00:34:06,378 --> 00:34:08,346
During the 44 days

649
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:09,547
of the bombardment,

650
00:34:09,781 --> 00:34:11,909
the 40 some square meters
of Kinmen

651
00:34:12,150 --> 00:34:14,118
was hit 47,000 times.

652
00:34:14,619 --> 00:34:15,916
After the battle broke out,

653
00:34:16,154 --> 00:34:18,816
the US provided
goods and armament assistance

654
00:34:19,057 --> 00:34:21,116
and escorted supplies
to the frontline,

655
00:34:21,359 --> 00:34:23,760
but avoided any direct interference.

656
00:34:29,634 --> 00:34:30,726
On October 23, Eisenhower

657
00:34:30,969 --> 00:34:33,461
and Chiang Kai-Shek
reached an understanding.

658
00:34:33,705 --> 00:34:34,365
Chiang agreed not to use

659
00:34:34,606 --> 00:34:36,973
armed force to counterattack China.

660
00:34:37,208 --> 00:34:41,372
Eisenhower promised to help
defense Kinmen and Matsu.

661
00:34:42,314 --> 00:34:43,179
This promise extended

662
00:34:43,415 --> 00:34:44,576
beyond the Mutual Defense Treaty

663
00:34:44,816 --> 00:34:46,910
signed by Taiwan and the US.

664
00:34:47,352 --> 00:34:48,478
The Aug. 23rd Artillery
Bombardment

665
00:34:48,720 --> 00:34:49,585
gradually concluded with

666
00:34:49,821 --> 00:34:52,188
the PRC adapting the method

667
00:34:52,424 --> 00:34:53,687
of attacking only on odd dates.

668
00:34:54,092 --> 00:34:55,082
But the real conclusion

669
00:34:55,327 --> 00:34:57,352
didn't come until 20 years later.

670
00:34:57,629 --> 00:34:58,596
The fierce military combat
across the strait

671
00:34:58,830 --> 00:35:00,491
gradually calms down to

672
00:35:00,732 --> 00:35:03,599
a Cold War situation.

673
00:35:03,969 --> 00:35:05,528
With no external conflicts,

674
00:35:05,770 --> 00:35:07,204
the republic government
was then able

675
00:35:07,439 --> 00:35:09,601
to exercise authoritative rule
on Taiwan

676
00:35:09,841 --> 00:35:11,673
and to fully develop its economy.

677
00:35:20,151 --> 00:35:21,744
Sharing the hatred
for a common enemy

678
00:35:21,987 --> 00:35:23,751
and having survived critical times,

679
00:35:23,989 --> 00:35:25,889
the people of Taiwan

680
00:35:26,124 --> 00:35:26,920
became an united

681
00:35:27,158 --> 00:35:29,252
life community.

682
00:35:29,527 --> 00:35:31,962
People were educated to call
themselves "Chinese,"

683
00:35:32,197 --> 00:35:34,495
honorable citizens of a "Free China.”

684
00:35:34,733 --> 00:35:36,360
They will never reconcile

685
00:35:36,601 --> 00:35:38,069
with the evil "Communist China.”

686
00:35:58,857 --> 00:36:00,188
October 31st,

687
00:36:00,425 --> 00:36:02,519
is the 70th birthday

688
00:36:02,761 --> 00:36:04,024
of our great leader
President Chiang.

689
00:36:04,262 --> 00:36:06,060
The whole country is
busy preparing

690
00:36:06,297 --> 00:36:08,095
for various kinds of celebrations.

691
00:36:08,533 --> 00:36:10,160
Facing the autocratic rule,

692
00:36:10,402 --> 00:36:12,496
intellectual liberalists from China

693
00:36:12,737 --> 00:36:15,707
such as Lei Zhen and Hu Shi

694
00:36:15,940 --> 00:36:18,238
cried out for freedom
and democracy.

695
00:36:18,510 --> 00:36:20,808
They founded the Free
China Journal.

696
00:36:21,179 --> 00:36:22,578
In 1956,

697
00:36:22,814 --> 00:36:25,181
on his 70th birthday,
Chiang announced

698
00:36:25,483 --> 00:36:28,350
his intension to serve another term.

699
00:36:28,887 --> 00:36:29,786
Free China Journal released

700
00:36:30,021 --> 00:36:32,115
the "Birthday Celebration
Special Issue.”

701
00:36:32,490 --> 00:36:35,084
Hu Shi, Hsu Fu-Kuan,
Mao Tse-Shui

702
00:36:35,326 --> 00:36:38,455
Hsu Dau-Lin, Chen Chi-Tien,
Tao Bai-Chuan,

703
00:36:38,697 --> 00:36:42,065
Chiang Yun-Tien,
Hsia Tao-Ping, and Lei Zhen,

704
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:43,597
are intellectual liberalists
from China.

705
00:36:43,835 --> 00:36:45,826
They took the opportunity

706
00:36:46,171 --> 00:36:47,468
to propose a self-review

707
00:36:47,706 --> 00:36:51,165
and to offer their advices
to Chiang Kai-Shek.

708
00:36:52,210 --> 00:36:54,975
Hu Shi wrote a long essay

709
00:36:55,213 --> 00:36:57,944
to tactfully advise Chiang
to give up dictatorship,

710
00:36:58,183 --> 00:37:00,914
to withdraw his power
from the government.

711
00:37:01,619 --> 00:37:03,553
Other essays advised Chiang

712
00:37:03,788 --> 00:37:05,347
to select a successor,

713
00:37:05,590 --> 00:37:06,887
to establish a cabinet system

714
00:37:07,125 --> 00:37:08,889
and to nationalize the armed forces.

715
00:37:15,366 --> 00:37:16,231
These advices were meant to

716
00:37:16,468 --> 00:37:18,197
offer the KMT an opportunity

717
00:37:18,436 --> 00:37:20,097
to reform itself.

718
00:37:20,338 --> 00:37:21,965
But they had exactly
the opposite effect

719
00:37:22,207 --> 00:37:24,608
and drew calculated critiques
in the KMT

720
00:37:24,843 --> 00:37:26,470
and military periodicals.

721
00:37:30,582 --> 00:37:33,517
From 1959 to 1960,

722
00:37:33,785 --> 00:37:35,184
Free China Journal
further expressed

723
00:37:35,420 --> 00:37:36,012
their disapproval of
Chiang's interference

724
00:37:36,254 --> 00:37:39,315
with the operation of the
constitution politics,

725
00:37:39,557 --> 00:37:42,026
making amendments
or revising the provisions

726
00:37:42,260 --> 00:37:44,991
for the purpose of renewing his term.

727
00:37:45,330 --> 00:37:46,559
These intellectuals have

728
00:37:46,798 --> 00:37:48,266
in fact slowly reached

729
00:37:48,500 --> 00:37:50,935
the KMT's limit.

730
00:37:57,208 --> 00:37:58,175
Six months after the publication of

731
00:37:58,409 --> 00:38:00,639
Free China Journal's special issue,

732
00:38:00,945 --> 00:38:02,743
Taiwan held its third election

733
00:38:02,981 --> 00:38:04,847
of county and city mayors,
and congressmen.

734
00:38:05,283 --> 00:38:06,045
Before the election,

735
00:38:06,284 --> 00:38:08,946
candidates from other parties joined

736
00:38:09,187 --> 00:38:10,780
a meeting on improving
election processes

737
00:38:11,022 --> 00:38:13,354
summoned by native politicians.

738
00:38:13,625 --> 00:38:14,319
They decided to have

739
00:38:14,559 --> 00:38:17,028
Lee Wan Chu organize

740
00:38:17,262 --> 00:38:19,560
an election review forum.

741
00:38:21,199 --> 00:38:23,258
On April 21st,

742
00:38:23,501 --> 00:38:25,265
voters of both sexes
across the island

743
00:38:25,503 --> 00:38:27,028
eagerly cast their ballots.

744
00:38:27,305 --> 00:38:30,297
The turnout rate was over 80%.

745
00:38:30,575 --> 00:38:32,009
Taiwan's self-rule

746
00:38:32,243 --> 00:38:34,211
and the democratic politics
of a free China

747
00:38:34,445 --> 00:38:36,709
took another step forward.

748
00:38:39,617 --> 00:38:40,550
In this election,

749
00:38:40,785 --> 00:38:42,253
Kuo Kuo-Chi of Taichung,

750
00:38:42,487 --> 00:38:43,784
Wu San-Lien of Tainan,

751
00:38:44,022 --> 00:38:45,421
Lee Yuan-Chan of Kaohsiung,

752
00:38:45,657 --> 00:38:47,091
Kuo Yu-Hsin of Yilan,

753
00:38:47,325 --> 00:38:48,724
Lee Wan-Chu of Yunlin,

754
00:38:48,960 --> 00:38:50,086
and Hsu Shih-Hsien of Chiayi

755
00:38:50,328 --> 00:38:51,727
were elected congressmen.

756
00:38:51,963 --> 00:38:54,057
They were later referred to

757
00:38:54,299 --> 00:38:56,825
as the Five Tigersor the
Five Dragons and One Phoenix.

758
00:39:03,041 --> 00:39:05,533
In 1960, there was
another local election.

759
00:39:05,777 --> 00:39:07,541
On May 18th,

760
00:39:07,779 --> 00:39:09,747
Lei Zhen, together with
politicians from outside KMT

761
00:39:09,981 --> 00:39:11,380
and from Chinese Youth Party

762
00:39:11,616 --> 00:39:12,947
and the China Democratic
Socialist Party, 72 in all,

763
00:39:13,184 --> 00:39:15,016
held a local election review

764
00:39:15,253 --> 00:39:18,245
for opposition party members
and non-partisans

765
00:39:18,489 --> 00:39:20,821
at the China Democratic
Socialist Party Headquarters,

766
00:39:21,059 --> 00:39:23,494
In the meeting, frauds in the
election were criticized.

767
00:39:23,728 --> 00:39:26,322
Kuo Kuo-Chi vehemently
declaimed at the review.

768
00:39:27,432 --> 00:39:30,766
I want to dissolve
the Chinese Youth Party

769
00:39:31,369 --> 00:39:33,098
and the China Democratic
Socialist Party,

770
00:39:33,338 --> 00:39:34,430
and to form a strong
opposition party

771
00:39:34,672 --> 00:39:36,436
with the democrats of Taiwan

772
00:39:37,075 --> 00:39:38,804
to enforce democracy.

773
00:39:40,211 --> 00:39:40,905
His speech

774
00:39:41,145 --> 00:39:41,976
pushed the party organization

775
00:39:42,213 --> 00:39:44,477
into an intense new stage.

776
00:39:46,117 --> 00:39:48,176
In 1960, the Vietnam War
broke out

777
00:39:48,419 --> 00:39:50,888
and Taiwan heightened
its anti-communist defense.

778
00:39:51,122 --> 00:39:52,385
On September 4th of the same year,

779
00:39:52,624 --> 00:39:53,853
the Taiwan Garrison Command

780
00:39:54,092 --> 00:39:56,891
arrested Lei Zhen, Fu Zheng,

781
00:39:57,128 --> 00:39:59,290
editor-in-chief
of Free China Journal,

782
00:39:59,530 --> 00:40:00,861
its manager Ma Chih-Su,

783
00:40:01,099 --> 00:40:03,067
and its booker Lei Chi-Yin.

784
00:40:03,334 --> 00:40:04,096
Lei Zhen was charged with

785
00:40:04,335 --> 00:40:05,894
"propagating for communists”

786
00:40:06,137 --> 00:40:07,935
by sending messages of
“hopeless of fighting back"

787
00:40:08,172 --> 00:40:10,732
and was sentenced to
10 years in jail.

788
00:40:11,075 --> 00:40:12,042
The arrest of Lei Zhen

789
00:40:12,277 --> 00:40:13,108
ended the valuable experience

790
00:40:13,344 --> 00:40:14,812
of Taiwanese and mainlanders

791
00:40:15,046 --> 00:40:17,174
working hand in hand

792
00:40:17,415 --> 00:40:18,644
to fight for a democratic Taiwan.

793
00:40:18,950 --> 00:40:20,645
Heartless strikes by the ruler

794
00:40:20,885 --> 00:40:22,478
with the Lei Zhen case

795
00:40:22,720 --> 00:40:25,018
sunk Taiwan's democratic
movement.

796
00:40:25,390 --> 00:40:26,516
And Free China Journal

797
00:40:26,758 --> 00:40:29,056
became an irony in history.

798
00:40:38,069 --> 00:40:40,697
In addition to suppressing
political democracy,

799
00:40:40,939 --> 00:40:43,135
after they arrive Taiwan,

800
00:40:43,374 --> 00:40:45,001
the KMT instilled anti-communist
thoughts in the people

801
00:40:45,243 --> 00:40:47,507
through education and
media monopoly.

802
00:40:48,313 --> 00:40:49,246
Besides suppressing
anything related to local culture

803
00:40:49,480 --> 00:40:51,312
and local cultural performances,

804
00:40:51,549 --> 00:40:54,177
the KMT also suppress

805
00:40:54,419 --> 00:40:54,977
any literary arts

806
00:40:55,219 --> 00:40:58,245
connected with socialism

807
00:40:58,523 --> 00:41:01,584
and inhibited the spread
of liberal thinking.

808
00:41:02,026 --> 00:41:03,084
Furthermore, they ignored
the achievements

809
00:41:03,328 --> 00:41:05,956
and developments made in
Taiwanese literature and art

810
00:41:06,197 --> 00:41:08,029
during Japanese Occupation.

811
00:41:09,133 --> 00:41:10,191
Living under

812
00:41:10,435 --> 00:41:13,029
a vacuum state of thinking

813
00:41:13,271 --> 00:41:15,467
and a spoon-fed education system,

814
00:41:15,707 --> 00:41:16,765
young people of Taiwan
spent a large amount of time

815
00:41:17,008 --> 00:41:19,136
memorizing materials about China.

816
00:41:19,377 --> 00:41:20,367
However, they didn't identify

817
00:41:20,611 --> 00:41:22,705
with the land they lived in

818
00:41:22,947 --> 00:41:24,381
and the people they lived with.

819
00:41:27,752 --> 00:41:28,548
At that time,

820
00:41:28,786 --> 00:41:31,016
most university graduates

821
00:41:31,255 --> 00:41:33,019
have two choices before them.

822
00:41:33,257 --> 00:41:35,589
They can get into the civil
service sector

823
00:41:35,827 --> 00:41:37,761
through various examinations

824
00:41:37,996 --> 00:41:39,361
for a life of stability.

825
00:41:43,468 --> 00:41:45,937
Or they can study abroad,

826
00:41:46,170 --> 00:41:49,196
temporarily or permanently
leaving Taiwan.

827
00:41:57,582 --> 00:41:59,414
Local concerns were ignored

828
00:41:59,650 --> 00:42:01,311
and history and culture
were disconnected.

829
00:42:01,552 --> 00:42:03,680
American values thus

830
00:42:03,921 --> 00:42:05,320
entered the country.

831
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:07,389
Bob Hope came to the stage

832
00:42:07,625 --> 00:42:09,423
sitting on a Chinese rickshaw

833
00:42:09,660 --> 00:42:12,095
and made the audience
crack in laughter.

834
00:42:19,904 --> 00:42:21,497
During the Vietnam War,

835
00:42:21,739 --> 00:42:24,606
Taiwan became
a logistic supply base

836
00:42:24,842 --> 00:42:26,901
and a holiday retreat for
the American armed forces.

837
00:42:27,712 --> 00:42:29,578
More than 200,000 Americans
visited Taiwan in 10 years.

838
00:42:29,814 --> 00:42:32,749
A large number of bars
and sex shops opened,

839
00:42:32,984 --> 00:42:35,282
forming Taiwan's early sex industry.

840
00:42:37,822 --> 00:42:38,653
Furthermore,

841
00:42:38,890 --> 00:42:41,086
Hollywood movies, anti-war songs,

842
00:42:41,325 --> 00:42:43,316
Coca-Cola, and American radios

843
00:42:43,561 --> 00:42:45,723
became fashionable.

844
00:43:00,044 --> 00:43:02,843
The KMT applied suppression
politically,

845
00:43:03,081 --> 00:43:05,709
but economically they
believed in technical experts

846
00:43:05,950 --> 00:43:08,681
to advance policies
and carry out reforms.

847
00:43:09,720 --> 00:43:12,212
People like Yin Chung-Jung,

848
00:43:13,224 --> 00:43:14,282
Lee Kuo-Ding

849
00:43:15,026 --> 00:43:16,118
and Yen Chia-Kan were trusted

850
00:43:16,360 --> 00:43:18,590
and had much freedom in their duty.

851
00:43:18,830 --> 00:43:21,697
They led in US Aid Council,

852
00:43:21,933 --> 00:43:23,958
International & Economic
Cooperation Council,

853
00:43:24,202 --> 00:43:26,796
and Economic Affairs Ministry,

854
00:43:27,038 --> 00:43:28,904
to help lay basis for later
economic progress.

855
00:43:30,274 --> 00:43:32,106
They effectively planned and used

856
00:43:32,343 --> 00:43:34,812
the funds from the U.S.
and foreign exchange

857
00:43:35,046 --> 00:43:38,175
to properly map out an
industrial development plan.

858
00:43:39,250 --> 00:43:40,479
In the 1960s,

859
00:43:40,718 --> 00:43:42,652
Taiwan's economy
began to transform.

860
00:43:42,887 --> 00:43:44,252
A large part was

861
00:43:44,489 --> 00:43:45,183
due to the implementation of

862
00:43:45,423 --> 00:43:47,482
an export-oriented economic policy

863
00:43:47,725 --> 00:43:50,057
and the establishment
of an export processing zone.

864
00:43:51,629 --> 00:43:52,562
In 1965,

865
00:43:52,797 --> 00:43:54,993
under the suggestion
of Lee Kuo-Ding,

866
00:43:55,233 --> 00:43:55,893
the world's first
export processing zone

867
00:43:56,134 --> 00:43:58,501
was established in Kaohsiung,

868
00:43:58,736 --> 00:44:00,170
allowing production materials

869
00:44:00,404 --> 00:44:03,169
to be imported without taxes

870
00:44:03,407 --> 00:44:04,670
of any kind.

871
00:44:04,909 --> 00:44:07,571
All products can be exported freely.

872
00:44:08,713 --> 00:44:10,306
The Kaohsiung Export
Processing Zone

873
00:44:10,548 --> 00:44:12,880
provided inexpensive
labor and land,

874
00:44:13,117 --> 00:44:14,812
tax incentives,

875
00:44:15,052 --> 00:44:16,542
and efficient management,

876
00:44:16,787 --> 00:44:18,653
to attract many foreign investments

877
00:44:18,890 --> 00:44:21,325
and create myriads of job
opportunities.

878
00:44:21,759 --> 00:44:23,318
In addition,

879
00:44:23,561 --> 00:44:25,290
there were the hard-working

880
00:44:25,530 --> 00:44:26,929
small and medium-sized
business owners.

881
00:44:27,231 --> 00:44:28,756
They worked industriously

882
00:44:29,000 --> 00:44:31,196
to produce and to develop
an international market.

883
00:44:31,435 --> 00:44:32,960
Working with the government,

884
00:44:33,204 --> 00:44:35,195
they created an economic miracle
in Taiwan.

885
00:44:36,908 --> 00:44:39,240
In the global sense,

886
00:44:39,477 --> 00:44:40,638
countries like Taiwan, Korea,

887
00:44:40,878 --> 00:44:42,312
Singapore, and Hong Kong,

888
00:44:42,547 --> 00:44:44,174
can provide human resources

889
00:44:44,415 --> 00:44:45,405
with cheap labor,

890
00:44:45,650 --> 00:44:48,085
and infrastructure.

891
00:44:48,319 --> 00:44:50,185
In the 1960s

892
00:44:50,421 --> 00:44:51,889
their economy began to grow

893
00:44:52,123 --> 00:44:54,854
and was called Asian Tigers.

894
00:44:58,896 --> 00:45:00,091
Industrial development, however,

895
00:45:00,331 --> 00:45:02,163
was at the cost of agriculture,

896
00:45:02,400 --> 00:45:04,425
and also sacrificed the
ecological environment.

897
00:45:04,669 --> 00:45:07,969
Rural villages provided an
abundance of cheap labor.

898
00:45:08,206 --> 00:45:11,005
Many country girls went to
cities for better jobs.

899
00:45:11,242 --> 00:45:14,439
This is quite common at that time.

900
00:45:15,379 --> 00:45:16,972
There's a popular song

901
00:45:17,215 --> 00:45:18,410
from the early 60s

902
00:45:18,649 --> 00:45:19,980
titled
"The Wish of an Orphan Girl."

903
00:45:20,218 --> 00:45:21,549
It represented
the sound of the people

904
00:45:21,786 --> 00:45:23,447
and voiced their meager hope.

905
00:45:42,907 --> 00:45:44,739
Under heavy oppression,

906
00:45:44,976 --> 00:45:48,071
life then was monotonous,
confined and repressed.

907
00:45:48,312 --> 00:45:49,040
The original vitality

908
00:45:49,280 --> 00:45:51,578
that existed in the society

909
00:45:51,816 --> 00:45:54,217
was duly directed

910
00:45:54,452 --> 00:45:56,477
under the government's
fiscal policy.

911
00:45:56,721 --> 00:45:59,053
Taiwan's future was moving
toward a new start.

912
00:46:03,461 --> 00:46:05,293
Taiwan's little league baseball team

913
00:46:05,529 --> 00:46:07,657
with an overwhelming edge

914
00:46:07,898 --> 00:46:09,297
easily won championship in

915
00:46:09,533 --> 00:46:12,434
Little League World Series.

916
00:46:26,417 --> 00:46:29,182
At two o'clock am
of August 20, 1969,

917
00:46:29,420 --> 00:46:30,410
most of the people in Taiwan

918
00:46:30,655 --> 00:46:32,680
were up listening to the radio

919
00:46:32,923 --> 00:46:35,153
broadcasting the Little
League World Series game

920
00:46:35,393 --> 00:46:36,986
held in Williamsport, Pennsylvania.

921
00:46:37,328 --> 00:46:37,954
When they heard that

922
00:46:38,195 --> 00:46:40,391
the Taichung Gold Dragon

923
00:46:40,631 --> 00:46:42,326
defeated
the U.S. West Division team

924
00:46:42,566 --> 00:46:45,092
and became world champion,

925
00:46:45,336 --> 00:46:46,735
the whole country burst into cheers.

926
00:46:46,971 --> 00:46:48,700
People ran out to the streets
and hugged one another.

927
00:46:48,939 --> 00:46:50,407
Sounds of firecrackers
can be heard everywhere.

928
00:46:51,175 --> 00:46:52,609
In the following ten years,

929
00:46:52,843 --> 00:46:53,401
little league baseball

930
00:46:53,644 --> 00:46:56,477
became the nation's hottest
leisure activity.

931
00:46:56,714 --> 00:46:59,183
Through the televised games
every August,

932
00:46:59,417 --> 00:47:01,715
the country participated
in the event with fervor.

933
00:47:02,253 --> 00:47:04,984
Baseball players became
idols to young kids

934
00:47:05,222 --> 00:47:08,021
and heroes to the Taiwanese people.

935
00:47:08,659 --> 00:47:10,593
In later diplomatic difficulties,

936
00:47:10,828 --> 00:47:11,693
it consoled the people of Taiwan

937
00:47:11,929 --> 00:47:14,296
for their frustrated national pride.

938
00:47:15,966 --> 00:47:17,400
After the winning team
received flowers from

939
00:47:17,635 --> 00:47:20,935
the students of Chongshan
Girls High School,

940
00:47:21,172 --> 00:47:22,196
they boarded army jeeps

941
00:47:22,440 --> 00:47:23,703
for a parade around the city

942
00:47:23,941 --> 00:47:26,035
filled with cheering crowds.

943
00:47:37,888 --> 00:47:39,982
International situations in the 1970s

944
00:47:40,224 --> 00:47:41,817
took a great turn.

945
00:47:42,059 --> 00:47:43,151
Taiwan was about to face

946
00:47:43,394 --> 00:47:46,796
a series of diplomatic failures.

947
00:47:47,298 --> 00:47:48,561
With the change in

948
00:47:48,799 --> 00:47:50,767
Taiwan's international position,

949
00:47:51,035 --> 00:47:52,366
the history of the Taiwanese people

950
00:47:52,603 --> 00:47:55,004
underwent a theatrical development.

951
00:48:00,511 --> 00:48:01,103
Taiwan began to look for

952
00:48:01,345 --> 00:48:03,712
its position

953
00:48:03,948 --> 00:48:06,042
under the realities
of international politics,

954
00:48:06,283 --> 00:48:09,742
and continued to advance
in a hard environment.

